A coffee shop in freezing Canada has received a shot of warmth after being yarn bombed.

A branch of Tim Hortons in Fort Frances, Ontario - where temperatures are set to plummet to minus 15 Celsius this weekend - has been coated in meters of wool thanks to  a needle-wielding army of locals.

Couches, floors and chairs appear covered in neat knots of thread with customers soaking in its soft touch.

