The sewing group even created a giant beanie hat to go on top of the restaurant, complete with the brand's logo. 

They then crocheted an equally large scarf to wrap around the store front, being careful not to seal the door.

Sticking to the company colors they selected scarlet red and white fibers.

On December 11 the town of Fort Frances was all abuzz over the mysterious 'yarn bombing' of trees, fire hydrants, mail boxes and even park benches around town. 

Two days later, the residents  woke up to long strings of red yarn all over town - leading them straight to the local Tim Hortons.

The Canadian coffee company picked the Fort Frances store for the stunt as it's known for being one of the coldest spots in North America.  

