It then went about gathering a volunteer crew together.

Gord McQuarrie, who owns the franchise, said the decision came as a big surprise to everyone, even him.  

He received a telephone call asking if he'd give up the store for a couple of days for a special project and willingly obliged.

'We have amazing guests at our Tim Hortons and I'm thrilled we were able to surprise them in this special way just in time for the holidays,' McQuarrie said.

'We succeeded in spreading warmth - we gave out hundreds of cups of free coffee and hot chocolate and everyone looked happy and comfortable inside the restaurant.'

To spread even more warmth, Tim Hortons is donating yarn to various knitting groups across the country to help knit warm accessories for people in need. The company is encouraging customers to spread the #WarmWishes.

 

